> Treat yourself to truffles with tonight's 'shroom-packed pasta. You'll start with penne, which you'll cook until tender, then toss in a silky, savory sauce of sautéed button mushrooms, garlic powder, mushroom stock, cream cheese, and Parmesan. A swirl of butter and dusting of truffle zest take the rich and umami flavors to the next level. Garnish everything with crunchy, garlicky panko, then pour yourself a glass of wine and toast to a restaurant-worthy dinner.

Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring, until golden and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Cook until just fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot of boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Stir in mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Stir scallion whites, remaining garlic powder, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) into pan with mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, half the @Parmesan cheese{1 1/2%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving), and @water{1/3%cup} (½ cup for 4). Cook, stirring, until combined and creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in tomato, another @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), and @truffle zest{2%g} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir drained penne into pan with sauce until thoroughly coated, adding water a splash at a time until sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Divide between bowls; top with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan. Sprinkle with as much garlicky panko as you like and serve.